images

9
00:00:43.776 --> 00:00:49.920
The Spectacle cannot be understood either as a deliberate distortion of the visual world or as a product of the technology of the mass 

10
00:00:50.176 --> 00:00:51.200
dissemination of images

11
00:00:51.456 --> 00:00:55.040
Is far better viewed as a weltanschauung that has been actualized

12
00:00:55.296 --> 00:00:57.088
translated into the material realm

13
00:00:57.344 --> 00:01:00.160
a world view transformed into an objective Force

14
00:01:00.928 --> 00:01:07.072
The whole life of those societies in which modern conditions of production prevail presents itself as an immense 

15
00:01:07.328 --> 00:01:08.608
accumulation of spectacles

16
00:01:08.864 --> 00:01:12.448
All that once was directly lived has become a mere representation

17
00:01:13.216 --> 00:01:17.056
Images detached from every aspect of life merge into a common stream

18
00:01:17.312 --> 00:01:19.872
and the former unity of life Is lost forever

19
00:01:20.384 --> 00:01:25.504
Apprehended in a partial way, reality unfolds in a new generality as a pseudo world apart

20
00:01:25.760 --> 00:01:27.808
solely as an object of contemplation

21
00:01:28.320 --> 00:01:34.464
the tendency towards the specialisation of images of the world finds it's highest expression in the world of the autonomous image

22
00:01:34.720 --> 00:01:36.768
where deceit deceives itself 

23
00:01:37.280 --> 00:01:43.168
The Spectacle in its generality is a concrete inversion of life and as such the autonomous movement of non-life

24
00:01:45.472 --> 00:01:46.752
The Spectacle appears

25
00:01:47.008 --> 00:01:48.800
at once as society itself

26
00:01:49.312 --> 00:01:50.592
as a part of society

27
00:01:50.848 --> 00:01:52.384
and as a means of unification

28
00:01:52.896 --> 00:01:58.016
As a part of society it is that sector where all attention, all consciousness converges

29
00:01:58.272 --> 00:02:04.160
Being isolated and precisely for that reason this sector is the locus of illusion and false consciousness

30
00:02:04.416 --> 00:02:08.000
The unity it imposes is merely the official language of generalized

31
00:02:08.256 --> 00:02:09.024
speculation

32
00:02:16.448 --> 00:02:22.592
The Spectacle appears at once as society itself, as a part of society, and as a means of unification

33
